Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{6%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until lightly browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Let cool for at least ~{5%minutes}.

== Salad ==

Meanwhile, remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%ounce}; chop into bite-size pieces. Halve, core, and thinly slice half the @apple{1}.

Place kale in a #large bowl{} and lightly season with @salt{}. Using your hands, massage kale (similar to how you would knead dough), until leaves are tender, ~{30-60%seconds}.

> To make kale even more tender, add a drizzle of olive oil along with salt before massaging.

== Beef ==

Pat @beef tenderloin filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @brown sugar bourbon seasoning{10.8%g}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

> Swap in beef for chicken. Cook to desired doneness, 4-7 minutes per side. Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add beef and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-7%minutes} per side.

Transfer to a #cutting board{}; let rest at least ~{5%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

Add @dried cranberries{1%ounce}, roasted carrots, and sliced apple to bowl with kale. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Reserve a half packet of @honey Dijon dressing{3%ounce} in a #small bowl{} for serving. Drizzle salad with remaining dressing to taste; toss to combine.

Thinly slice beef against the grain.

Divide salad between bowls and top with beef. Drizzle with reserved dressing. Sprinkle with @sunflower seeds{1/2%ounce} and serve.